      "mode": "markdown",
      "options": {
        "content": "**Current scope**: shared, engine-agnostic Pod/Agent resource monitoring. The lower socket / network / filesystem charts stay on run-scoped aggregate gauges (`ptp_run_pod_*`) so child-panel legends keep stable `pod_ip / node_label / agent_host` context instead of falling back to ambiguous container ids. `Memory Working Set` now prefers run-scoped memory-used bytes and only falls back to cAdvisor working-set bytes when that host/runtime gauge is absent, so the same shared dashboard still reads as a multi-Pod monitor. Container-level fallback scope should come from run metadata when available and otherwise fall back to a wildcard regex instead of a fixed `ptp-agent.*` naming assumption. **Runtime scope semantics**: host / EC2 runtime shows machine-level resource usage, while docker / K8S runtime shows container-level resource usage. These two scopes should not be compared as if they shared the same denominator. For host / EC2 runtime, network and filesystem panels may intentionally stay empty because this workspace does not publish reliable process-scope host bytes counters on macOS; empty here means **withheld to avoid misleading totals**, not a broken pipeline. The dashboard presents four CPU/Memory summary cards first, then overview, CPU/Memory, network and filesystem resource charts. Run-scoped context is limited to run_id filtering; no chart depends on engine-specific request or error metrics.",
